<HL>
   Bayly Corp. Retains Bear Stearns
</HL>
<DATE>
08/08/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   BAYL
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   DENVER -- Bayly Corp. said it retained Bear, Stearns &amp; Co.
as a financial adviser to help the company review options
including a merger or recapitalization.
   "We're not ruling anything out," said George K. Hansen,
chairman and chief executive officer of the apparel
manufacturer. "This has been a troubled company for two years
now."
